  "prompt": "Can I use my debit card as credit card on Airbnb?",
  "response": "Yes, you can typically use a debit card on Airbnb as a payment method. When booking, you'll enter your debit card details just like you would with a credit card. However, there are a few things to keep in mind:\n\n1. Airbnb will usually place a pre-authorization hold on your card for the estimated total of your stay.\n\n2. Some debit cards may have daily spending limits that could impact your booking.\n\n3. Some hosts may prefer credit cards due to additional protections and guarantees.\n\n4. Using a debit card might result in a temporary hold on funds in your bank account.\n\n5. Credit cards often provide additional travel protections that debit cards do not.\n\nWhile you can use a debit card, a credit card is generally recommended for easier booking and added travel protections.",
